  gatheringCharacters:
  - characterName: Ozric
    characterObject: {fileID: 590094279}
    characterButton: {fileID: 590094281}
    characterRectTransform: {fileID: 590094280}
    normalPosition: {x: -690, y: -107}
    focusedPosition: {x: -690, y: -107}
    introLinesBeforeChoices:
    - Ozric bows his head slightly
    - "\u201CGood morning.\u201D\r\n"
    - You sit down opposite of him.
    - "\u2026\r\n"
    - "\u201CI saw you speaking to Ash yesterday.\u201D"
    - His statement catches you off guard.
    - "\u201CShould I not have?\u201D"
    - Ozric shakes his head.
    - "\u201CYou are free to speak with whomever you wish.\u201D"
    - "\u2026"
    - "\u201CAlthough I do perceive his company as unsettling\u2026\u201D"
    - ' He finally takes a spoonful of stew.

'
    - "\u201CHe asks too many questions\u2026 \u201C"
    - "\u201CQuestions lead souls away from saving.\u201D"
    - "\u2026"
    - "\u201CStill \u2013 you are new.\u201D"
    - "\u201CThere is much for you to learn.\u201D"
    - "\u201CAnd much for me to teach.\u201D\r\n"
    - A faint smile appears on his face.
    - "\u201CIf you are willing.\u201D"
    - You nod.
    - "\u201CTeach me what?\u201D"
    - Ozric sets down his spoon.
    - "\u201CPatience\u2026 Discipline\u2026 Devotion\u2026\u201D"
    - "\u2026"
    - "\u201CThe things I lacked when I first arrived.\u201D"
    - 'He studies you carefully.

'
    - "\u201CI was much like you one, you know.\u201D"
    - "\u201CLost\u2026 Angry\u2026\u201D"
    - "\u201CThen the Leader found me.\u201D"
    - A faint smile appears on his face.
    - "\u201CI owe him everything.\u201D"
    - "\u201CA debt that I can truly never repay.\u201D"
    - "\u2026"
    - ' Ozric quietly resumes eating.'
    - For a while, neither of you speak.
    - "\u2026"
    - "\u201CMany mistake doubt for wisdom.\u201D"
    - "\u201CI used to. Now I know better.\u201D"
    - "\u2026"
    - Ozric picks up his bowl to his mouth to finish the rest of the stew.
    - "\u2026"
    - After putting the empty dish back on the table, he gives you a slight nod.
    - "\u201CForgive me, I have duties to attend to.\u201D"
    - "\u201CShould you wish to learn more\u2026\u201D"
    - "\u201C\u2026 you only need to ask.\u201D"
    - "\u201CMay the Flesh embrace you.\u201D"
    - "\u2026"
    - 'As Ozric turns to leave, his offer lingers in your mind.

'
    - "\u201CWait.\u201D"
    - Surprised, Ozric turns around.
    - You pull out a card.
